practitioner.about:
Dr. Azhari Elawad is a Specialist in ENT and Head and Neck Surgery at Medcare Medical Centre. He completed his MBBS from the Faculty of Medicine, University of Craiova, Romania and a PhD in Otolaryngology from Hacettepe Hospital University in Ankara, Turkey. He is a member of the Turkish Society of Otolaryngology, the Emirates Otolaryngology Medical Association, the Sudanese Otolaryngology Society, the PAN Arab Rhinology Society and the Inter-American Association of Paediatric Otolaryngology. 

Dr. ELawad has rich global experience of over three decades in ENT Surgeries and coblation, having attended training courses across Turkey, India, and Spain. He also received invaluable teaching experience working at the Khartoum Teaching Hospital in Sudan and the Hacettepe Teaching Hospital in Ankara as an Assistant Professor. Initially, he worked as an ENT doctor at Hacettepe Hospital in Ankara and then as an ENT specialist at the Ministry of Health, Al Qassimi Hospital, and Kuwaiti Hospital in UAE. For a few years, he worked in his private clinic while, at the same time working as a visiting doctor at Corniche Hospital, the Emirates International Hospital and Oriana Hospital, Sharjah in the the UAE. Before joining Medcare, he worked as an ENT Specialist at the Sharjah Corniche Medical Center and Amina Healthcare Group. After completing a course on coblation surgery in Barcelona, Spain, he has been working with coblation to treat snoring, tonsils and adenoids. 

Dr. Elawad’s expertise covers all aspects of otolaryngology. He conducts regular ENT clinics treating all patients with ENT problems and performs all routine ENT surgeries like tonsils, adenoids, septoplasties, SMR, SMD by coblation, tympanoplasties, and mastoid surgeries. He also performs micro-laryngoscopies and microscopic ear surgery. He is proficient in minor procedures carried out in the outpatient clinic including fibre optic nasopharyngoscopy, microscopic ear examination, endoscopic nasal examination, removing foreign bodies from ears nose and throat, usual medical disorders of the ears nose and throat, treating of vertigo by hall pike manoeuvre, treating all fungal ear infections, removing of ear wax by suction or by ear wash, treating of nasal bleeding or post nasal bleeding by the nasal pack or nasal cautery (chemical or electrical), maxillary sinuses washout and treating swelling of ear canals due to Otitis Externa by special manoeuvre. He also treats patients with allergic rhinitis, sinusitis and nasal polyps and cures snoring through coblation.

Dr. Elawad attends Otolaryngology conferences in Dubai regularly. He has contributed greatly to the spread of information and knowledge about his field by writing medical books for university students as well as posting medical advice on his personal TikTok account. He enjoys reading and writing and has a passion for sharing his learnings with others. During his spare time, he likes playing sports too. He is fluent in Arabic, English, Romanian and Turkish.

The centre takes pride in its extensive array of stateof-the-art equipment, empowering its highly skilled medical team to deliver a premium level of care to all patients.
